[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare triage bot decomposes into ten logical stages: channel entry, input safety screening with continuous-emergency-screening, identity-and-chart-context loading, symptom identification and protocol selection, structured protocol-driven questioning, clinical-decision-rule computation, acuity scoring and recommendation, output safety screening with conservative-bias verification, recommendation delivery, and nurse-line escalation when applicable. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.5 carry forward; this recipe adds four new ones (clinical-protocol-corpus governance with medical-director sign-off, conservative-bias-default policy, continuous-emergency-screening pipeline, and FDA-strategy-alignment artifact maintenance).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CHANNEL ENTRY ─────────────────────────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Patient opens chat in institution's app, member        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    portal, telehealth front-door, employer-side wellness  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    portal, or via SMS/voice channel]                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Greeting and disclosure]                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Identifies as a chatbot                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - States scope (informational triage, not diagnosis,   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      not replacement for a clinician)                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Notes the questions are based on the same protocols  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      institutional nurses use                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Names the human-escalation pathway                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reinforces the 911 redirect for any emergency        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Conversation session bootstrap]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generate session_id                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Capture channel, authentication context, deep-link   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      parameters (e.g., a specific symptom topic the       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      patient tapped to start the conversation)            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: session_id, channel, auth context, deep-link   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    parameters]                                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── INPUT SAFETY + CONTINUOUS EMERGENCY SCREEN ────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Standard input safety primitives from recipe 11.1]     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Prompt-injection detection                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - PHI minimization                                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Self-harm and crisis classifier                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Triage-specific continuous emergency screening]        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Runs on every patient utterance, not just first      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Detects explicit emergency presentations             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (active chest pain, stroke symptoms, severe          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      bleeding, suspected anaphylaxis, suspected           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      overdose, acute psychosis, suicidal intent)          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Detects emergency feature constellations             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (cauda equina pattern, sepsis pattern, abdominal     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      catastrophe pattern, neurological deficit pattern)   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Detects pediatric-specific emergency presentations   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (febrile infant, lethargic infant, suspected         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      meningitis pattern, suspected intussusception)       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Triggers immediate 911 / 988 / institutional crisis  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      routing with stay-on-the-line guidance               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: input passes / input blocked-with-disposition  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    / emergency-routed-immediately]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── IDENTITY AND CHART-CONTEXT LOADING ────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Authenticated session path (recommended default)]      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient is logged into the institution's app or      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      portal                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Session conveys verified patient_id and chart        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      access scope                                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Unauthenticated path (limited scope)]                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - For lower-stakes general health questions, the bot   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      may answer without authentication, with reduced      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      protocol scope and explicit "I don't know your       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      medical history" framing                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - High-acuity protocols and chart-aware                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      recommendations require authentication               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Pediatric and proxy-completion handling]               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Parent or guardian completing the conversation       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      for a minor child: the conversation is on            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      behalf of the child, with appropriate consent        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      handling per state law                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Adult-on-behalf-of-adult (caregiver, authorized      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      representative) with appropriate scope               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Chart-context tools]                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Demographics (age, sex, language preferences,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pediatric vs adult)                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active problem list                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active medication list (focused on those relevant    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      to common presenting symptoms: anticoagulants,       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      immunosuppressives, opioids, antidiabetics, etc.)    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Recent visit history (90 days)                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active treatment plans (oncology, transplant,        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      pregnancy, etc. that materially change triage)       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Known allergies                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Advance directives (where the institution stores)    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: verified patient_id, chart context, scope,     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    pediatric-vs-adult flag, proxy-completion flag]        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── SYMPTOM IDENTIFICATION + PROTOCOL SELECTION ───┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Symptom identification]                                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Free-form initial complaint mapped to symptom        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      category                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - LLM with retrieval over protocol library             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multi-symptom presentations: select highest-acuity-  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      eligible protocol; cross-reference others            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Protocol selection]                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Each symptom maps to one or more institutional       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      protocols                                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Protocols are versioned, owned by medical director   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      and nurse-line operations                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pediatric vs adult versions selected based on        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      patient age                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Special-population protocols (pregnancy, oncology    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      treatment, transplant, etc.) selected based on       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      chart context                                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Ambiguous-mapping handling]                            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot asks one or two clarifying questions when        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      multiple protocols are plausible                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Falls back to broad initial-assessment protocol      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      that branches based on responses                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Out-of-scope handling]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Some presentations are out of scope for the bot      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (e.g., suspected ingestion in a pediatric patient    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      where the institution's policy defers to Poison      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      Control)                                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Out-of-scope presentations route immediately to      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      the appropriate human resource                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: selected_protocol, protocol_version, fallback  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    or escalation marker if applicable]                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── STRUCTURED PROTOCOL-DRIVEN QUESTIONING ────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Bot conducts the protocol's question sequence]         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Canonical questions specified by the protocol        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - LLM may rephrase for clarity                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Order may adjust based on what the patient has       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      volunteered                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Ambiguous answers trigger follow-up                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot does not skip protocol questions                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Bot does not invent new questions outside the        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      protocol's scope                                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Continuous emergency screening (parallel)]             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Every patient response screened for emergency        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      content                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Mid-conversation emergency triggers immediate        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      911 / 988 routing                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Pediatric-specific question adaptations]               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Pediatric protocols ask the parent / caregiver       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Different vital-sign expectations                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Different emergency feature sets                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Conversation-state persistence]                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Each turn captured in conversation log               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Each protocol answer captured in structured form     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls audited                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: structured answer set per protocol question;   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    flag set for any emergency-screen triggers]            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── CLINICAL-DECISION-RULE COMPUTATION ────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Where the protocol invokes a clinical-decision rule:]  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - HEART score for chest pain                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Wells score for PE / DVT                             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Centor score for streptococcal pharyngitis           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Ottawa ankle / knee rules for ankle / knee injury    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - PERC rule for PE risk stratification                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Other institution-validated rules                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Each rule runs as a deterministic tool]                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Inputs: structured features captured during          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      questioning                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Outputs: score, risk stratum, recommended care       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      level per the rule's published thresholds            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool version audited                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [LLM does not compute the rule]                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - LLM gathers inputs                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool computes score                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - LLM presents the result                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: structured rule scores with risk strata and    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    rule-mapped care-level recommendations]                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── ACUITY SCORING + RECOMMENDATION ───────────────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Combine protocol decision logic with rule outputs]     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Protocol-driven recommendation from answer set       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Rule-driven recommendation where applicable          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - When recommendations diverge, the higher-acuity      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      recommendation wins (conservative default)           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Care-level recommendation set]                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - 911 (emergency response, do-not-self-transport)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Emergency department (urgent presentation; self-     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      transport with caveats; sometimes specific           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      institutional ED)                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Urgent care (within 24 hours; specific institutional │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      urgent care identified where possible)               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Primary care (today, in 24-48 hours, or routine      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      follow-up)                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Telehealth visit (synchronous video / voice; some    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      protocols recommend telehealth as the appropriate    │
